Tally Brown https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tally_Brown 0 Tally Brown (August 1, 1924 in New York City–May 6, 1989 in New York City) was a singer and actress who was part of the New York underground performance scene, particularly Andy Warhol's "Factory" and who appeared in or was the subject of films by Warhol and Rosa von Praunheim.
